OL,7,FHe will serve two-thirds of his
OL,8,Fsentence in custody and on his release
OL,9,Fwill be banned from driving for seven
OL,10,Fyears.
OL,12,FPreston Crown Court heard that Platt
OL,13,Fpersistently viewed content on his
OL,14,Fphone during a three-hour journey from
OL,15,FDumfries, Scotland, along the M6 and
OL,16,Fthen when he joined the westbound
OL,17,Fcarriageway of the M58.
