OL,7,FHe said: "Even though the defendant's
OL,8,Fmobile phone was in a cradle and in
OL,9,Ffront of him, this case provides an
OL,10,Fobject lesson in demonstrating that
OL,11,Feven for the most experienced of
OL,12,Fdrivers, not giving the road your
OL,13,Fundivided attention and concentration
OL,14,Fcan have the most devastating
OL,15,Fconsequences."
OL,17,FPlatt, a HGV driver for 15 years, was
OL,18,Fdescribed as "hating himself" for the
OL,19,Ftrauma he had caused.
